The baseball playoffs, which are underway now, involve 12 teams.  Since you can't wind down to two teams when you start with 12, the top four teams, based on season won-lost records, sit out the first round, while the others play the first round.  Those top teams automatically advance to the next round.  This is called a BYE.  After the other eight teams play the first round, four teams emerge, and they play the four teams who had a bye.  Eight now goes down to four, then to two, who play in the World Series for the championship.

The NFL also used the term BYE slightly differently.  Every team plays 17 games, but the season is 18 weeks long.  Each team has a week off, and that week is referred to as a BYE for that team.

